# migrated from tests/cases/prosepage.chat (gen346, hermetic + isolated)
[mock hermetic]
!set PARROT0_BASE=
!set PARROT0_SESSION=
!set PARROT0_WORLD_FACTS=0
!set PARROT0_LANG=en
!reset

[test prosepage]
# deep-reasoning M2 (docs/plans/deep-reasoning.md §8): the PROSE extractor. A DEEP
# read of a corpus page runs each sentence of its `## Extract` lead paragraph
# through the SAME comprehension parser M0 extended (extract_class_statement, now
# in extract-only mode so the simple "X is a Y" is asserted too), and every fact
# carries its source fragment (M1). Broad by design (§4.4): it over-extracts
# (capital(paris) is a partitive mis-read) and that is tolerated — the loop
# re-checks facts against their source (M4). Pages are curated static snapshots in
# kb/learning/pages/ (paris/france/whale/mammal), read even in the hermetic suite.

> read the page on Paris
< From the paris page I extracted 2 facts: capital(paris), located_in(paris, france).
# each extracted fact remembers the exact sentence it came from (M1 provenance).
> where did you learn about paris?
< I learned capital(paris) from: "paris is the capital of france"; located_in(paris, france) from: "paris is located in france".

> read the page on whale
< From the whale page I extracted 2 facts: mammal(whale), aquatic_animal(whale).
# an extracted membership is real, queryable knowledge.
> is a whale a mammal?
< Yes.

# honest: a topic with no curated page yields no facts, never invented.
> read the page on Xyzzy
< I don't have a page with extractable facts on xyzzy.

